---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE.name}>
  <h1>{SITE.name}</h1>

  <p class="contact-row">
    <a href={SITE.githubUrl}>{SITE.githubLabel}</a>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>{SITE.emailDisplay}</span>
  </p>

  <p>
    I’m an undergraduate at UC Berkeley interested in systems, machine learning
    infrastructure, algorithms, and hardware-aware optimization. I like the gap
    between high-level model code and the hardware it runs on — memory movement,
    kernel design, accelerator utilization, and why theoretically simple
    operations can behave very differently in practice.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <p>
      I’m profiling VAE decoder memory usage for video diffusion models and
      building Conv3D benchmarks that compare PyTorch/cuDNN against custom Triton
      kernels. Alongside that I’ve been writing accelerator-specific kernels on
      AWS Neuron (NKI) and reading more deeply into computer architecture,
      compilers, and efficient ML systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Selected work</h2>
    <dl class="worklist">
      <dt>Altair Chess Engine</dt>
      <dd>
        A UCI chess engine that reached superhuman strength and has received
        thousands of downloads.
      </dd>

      <dt>Conv3D benchmarking</dt>
      <dd>Correctness and performance infrastructure for realistic video VAE workloads.</dd>

      <dt>3D RoPE NKI kernel</dt>
      <dd>An accelerator-specific implementation of 3D rotary positional embeddings on AWS Neuron.</dd>
    </dl>
    <p class="more-link">
      <a href="/projects">All projects →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
